{"info": {"author": "Daniel Schick, et. al.", "author_email": "schick.daniel@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "# udkm1Dsim\n\nThe udkm1Dsim toolbox is a collection of Python classes and routines \nto simulate the structural dynamics and the according X-ray \ndiffraction response in one-dimensional sample structures after \nultrafast excitation. \nThe toolbox provides the capabilities to define arbitrary layered \nstructures on the atomic level including a rich database of \nelement-specific physical properties. \nThe excitation of ultrafast dynamics is represented by an \nN-temperature-model which is commonly applied for ultrafast \noptical excitations. \nStructural dynamics due to thermal stresses are calculated by \na linear-chain model of masses and springs. \nThe resulting X-ray diffraction response is computed by dynamical \nX-ray theory. \nThe udkm1Dsim toolbox is highly modular and allows to introduce \nuser-defined results at any step in the simulation procedure.\n\nThe udkm1Dsim toolbox was developed in the Ultrafast Dynamics \nin Condensed Matter group of Prof. Matias Bargheer at the \nUniversity of Potsdam, Germany. \nThe toolbox is currently maintained by Daniel Schick.\n\n## Documentation\nThe documentation can be found at [readthedocs.io](http://udkm1Dsim.readthedocs.io).\n\n## Citation\n\nPlease cite the following article if you use the udkm1Dsim toolbox for your own publications:\n\nD. Schick, A. Bojahr, M. Herzog, R. Shayduk, C. von Korff Schmising & M. Bargheer,\n*udkm1Dsim - A Simulation Toolkit for 1D Ultrafast Dynamics in Condensed Matter*,\n[Comput. Phys. Commun. 185, 651 (2014)](http://doi.org/10.1016/j.cpc.2013.10.009) [(preprint)](http://www.udkm.physik.uni-potsdam.de/medien/udkm1Dsim/udkm1DsimManuscriptPrePrint.pdf).\n\n## Installation\n\nYou can either install directly from pypi.org using the command\n\n    pip install udkm1Dsim\n\nor if you want to work on the latest develop release you can clone \nudkm1Dsim from the main git repository:\n\n    git clone https://github.com/dschick/udkm1Dsim.git udkm1Dsim\n\nTo work in editable mode (source is only linked \nbut not copied to the python site-packages), just do:\n\n    pip install -e ./udkm1Dsim\n\nOr to do a normal install with\n\n    pip install ./udkm1Dsim\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/dschick/udkm1Dsim", "keywords": "ultrafast dynamics condensed matter 1D", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "udkm1Dsim", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/udkm1Dsim/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/udkm1Dsim/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/dschick/udkm1Dsim"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/udkm1Dsim/0.1.4/", "requires_dist": ["tqdm", "numpy", "pint", "pytest", "scipy", "sympy", "tabulate", "dask ; extra == 'parallel'"], "requires_python": ">=3.5", "summary": "A Python Simulation Toolkit for 1D Ultrafast Dynamics in Condensed Matter", "version": "0.1.4", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>udkm1Dsim</h1>\n<p>The udkm1Dsim toolbox is a collection of Python classes and routines\nto simulate the structural dynamics and the according X-ray\ndiffraction response in one-dimensional sample structures after\nultrafast excitation.\nThe toolbox provides the capabilities to define arbitrary layered\nstructures on the atomic level including a rich database of\nelement-specific physical properties.\nThe excitation of ultrafast dynamics is represented by an\nN-temperature-model which is commonly applied for ultrafast\noptical excitations.\nStructural dynamics due to thermal stresses are calculated by\na linear-chain model of masses and springs.\nThe resulting X-ray diffraction response is computed by dynamical\nX-ray theory.\nThe udkm1Dsim toolbox is highly modular and allows to introduce\nuser-defined results at any step in the simulation procedure.</p>\n<p>The udkm1Dsim toolbox was developed in the Ultrafast Dynamics\nin Condensed Matter group of Prof. Matias Bargheer at the\nUniversity of Potsdam, Germany.\nThe toolbox is currently maintained by Daniel Schick.</p>\n<h2>Documentation</h2>\n<p>The documentation can be found at <a href=\"http://udkm1Dsim.readthedocs.io\" rel=\"nofollow\">readthedocs.io</a>.</p>\n<h2>Citation</h2>\n<p>Please cite the following article if you use the udkm1Dsim toolbox for your own publications:</p>\n<p>D. Schick, A. Bojahr, M. Herzog, R. Shayduk, C. von Korff Schmising &amp; M. Bargheer,\n<em>udkm1Dsim - A Simulation Toolkit for 1D Ultrafast Dynamics in Condensed Matter</em>,\n<a href=\"http://doi.org/10.1016/j.cpc.2013.10.009\" rel=\"nofollow\">Comput. Phys. Commun. 185, 651 (2014)</a> <a href=\"http://www.udkm.physik.uni-potsdam.de/medien/udkm1Dsim/udkm1DsimManuscriptPrePrint.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">(preprint)</a>.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>You can either install directly from pypi.org using the command</p>\n<pre><code>pip install udkm1Dsim\n</code></pre>\n<p>or if you want to work on the latest develop release you can clone\nudkm1Dsim from the main git repository:</p>\n<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/dschick/udkm1Dsim.git udkm1Dsim\n</code></pre>\n<p>To work in editable mode (source is only linked\nbut not copied to the python site-packages), just do:</p>\n<pre><code>pip install -e ./udkm1Dsim\n</code></pre>\n<p>Or to do a normal install with</p>\n<pre><code>pip install ./udkm1Dsim\n</code></pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6515970, "releases": {"0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "5d16376fbc44556c8177d8428e8d5fa7", "sha256": "aced604285c92eeb0ddabe1360154e542929ac2853f195f92c9ef8314d7358dd"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "udkm1Dsim-0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "5d16376fbc44556c8177d8428e8d5fa7", "packagetype": "sdist